Great! Let's start with `app.js`, the main application file that initializes Express and sets up middleware. Here's the initial setup:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.use(express.json());

// TODO: Add routes here

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

